Class
Description
BaseDAOException
The BaseDAOException class is the super class and the main triggering point for all DAO-layer sub-classes.
BaseDTO
The BaseDTO class enables sub-type polymorphism for DTO implementation.
BaseServiceException
The BaseServiceException class is the super class and the main triggering point for all Service-layer sub-classes.
BaseValidator
The BaseValidator class is an abstract class offering common methods for all its sub-classes.
Customer
The Customer class is an in-app representation of the Customer primary table.
CustomerDAOImpl
The CustomerDAOImpl class implements the CRUD methods defined in the IPrimaryEntityDAO interface for the Customer primary table.

The CustomerDeleteDAOException class is triggered when there is an error in the SQL DELETE FROM operation.

CustomerNotFoundException
The CustomerNotFoundException class is triggered when the specified Customer record is not found in the database.
CustomerServiceImpl
The CustomerServiceImpl class implements the methods defined in the IService interface for the Customer primary table.
CustomerUpdateDAOException
The CustomerUpdateDAOException class is triggered when there is an error in the SQL UPDATE operation.
DBUtil
The DBUtil class is responsible for establishing connections to the database.
IGenericEntity
The IGenericEntity provides common metrics to the IPrimaryEntityDAO and IJoinEntityDAO interfaces.
InvalidKeywordDAOException
The InvalidKeywordDAOException is triggered when there is an error after an incorrectly-formed SQL query.
IPrimaryEntityDAO<T>
The IPrimaryEntityDAO interface provides the CRUD method definitions for primary entities.
IService<T,E>
The IService interface contains the Service-level definitions of the CRUD wrapper methods and common metrics.
KeywordType
The KeywordType enum class provides standardized search terms for use by the DAO, Service, and viewcontroller layers.
Main
The Main class is the driver class of the application.
Menu

NoDataProvidedException
